FBIS4-48473 "drafr098_e_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 WEST AFRICA Liberia WFP Suspends Food Aid Deliveries to Tubmanburg WFP Suspends Food Aid Deliveries to Tubmanburg AB1905192394 London BBC World Service in English 1705 GMT 19 May 94 AB1905192394 London BBC World Service English BFN [From the "African News" segment of the "Focus on Africa" program] [Text] The United Nations' World Food Program [WFP] in Liberia is suspending its deliveries of food aid to Tubmanburg, the headquarters of the divided ULIMO [United Liberation Movement for Democracy in Liberia] faction. A WFP spokesman said it was acting because of the poor security situation and threats to its personnel. He said three aid vehicles had been seized by Mandingo supporters of Alhaji Koromah, and three others looted by Krahn of Koromah's rival, Roosevelt Johnson.
